  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [ ] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (3858d18 2022-10-23T12:18:26.3206418Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\n_No response_\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen I replayed a transaction, I encountered a strange phenomenon. There is a judgment inside the transaction: it needs to run under the specified block, otherwise it will be REVERT, so I set the block height when fork. 22556410, the simulation is successful;\r\n\r\nAt this time, the fork node is still running, I want to use anvil_reset to reset to the original block height of 22556410, and continue to replay the same transaction, but the transaction fails;\r\n\r\nI'm wondering what's causing this, doesn't anvil_reset reset the state of the entire Evm?\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n// fork options\r\nanvil -f https://bsc-mainnet.nodereal.io/v1/a9d5920ea85349c298ee543d3d4922ac  --chain-id  56 --gas-limit 12000000000000000000 --gas-price 9000000000000000000   --fork-block-number 22556410\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n// anvil_reset\r\n\r\npro.send(\"anvil_reset\",\r\n            [\r\n             {\r\n               chainId : 56,\r\n               forking: {\r\n                 jsonRpcUrl: \"https://bsc-mainnet.nodereal.io/v1/a9d5920ea85349c298ee543d3d4922ac\",\r\n                 blockNumber: 22556410,\r\n               },\r\n             },\r\n           ]\r\n         )\r\n\r\n// blockNumber = 22556410\r\nlet blockNumber= await pro.send('eth_blockNumber'); \r\n```",
